  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6609.44 sitting just 2 points below the GEX flip at 6607 and massive positive gamma wall at 6610 (+179.7B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above 6610 to hedge their long gamma exposure. The PIN regime combined with this concentrated gamma structure creates a tight trading range, with dealers providing natural resistance at 6610-6615 levels while offering support on any dip toward 6605. The gex_surge event and extreme short-term percentage changes (41.9% 1-min, 76.3% 5-min) indicate heightened option flow activity that's reinforcing these gamma walls.\n\nKey strikes: Watch 6610 as immediate resistance where dealer selling intensifies, 6607 flip level as the regime boundary, and 6605 support where gamma turns more favorable for upside moves.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6605-6610 with dealers capping upside moves.",
